09/06/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- The opposition Socialist Party (SP) launched a series of regional conferences on agriculture in the northern town of Shkodra on Sunday (June 8th). 
"This is the largest and most serious process ever taken up by a political force in Albania, which is seriously preparing to govern starting from next year," SP leader Edi Rama said. 
The party plans to hold 12 regional conferences around Albania as part of its initiative. 
(News 24, Top News, TVSH - 08/06/08)
